\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n9b5f8475-170a-4455-a4e2-1f771827469e,Artorious Wealth,,Institutional,63173c4e-768d-47fb-b470-465fd4b76342,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.153131,2026-03-12 09:42:25.153131,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Jordan Williams,jordan.williams@artorius.com,\na3cc45e1-b959-4a69-bc1b-891f430b7970,Avignon,,Institutional,47ba0f55-4e40-4dd2-85e0-4c97c50255ff,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.159437,2026-03-12 09:42:25.159437,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Nick Cliffe,nick@avignoncapital.com,\naf7da5b9-d8b3-4051-8dfa-0c64eb4e836d,Chu (HK),,Institutional,eb75b700-4ca1-48a2-960a-6abfa05fe52d,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.244374,2026-03-12 09:42:25.244374,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"1. Preferably Freehold \r\n2. ⁠Single tenant \r\n3. ⁠Preferably located in a major tourist attraction in the west end \r\n3. ⁠with over 5 years to expiry and tenant has no break option\r\n4. ⁠zone 1\r\n5. ⁠NiY over 6% with upside \r\n6. ⁠upward rent review only \r\n7. ⁠close to main underground stations\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\nf512d013-ae3a-40bb-ab36-0a36fe1ab635,Canada Life,,Institutional,6bbec457-a399-43af-8f79-90a361dea48a,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.213398,2026-03-12 09:42:25.213398,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,James Ogborne,James.ogborne@canadalife.co.uk,\n03d82f7f-80d6-4999-b3b8-332d0bb0b562,Capco Shaftesbury,,Institutional,7e06f68c-2d92-42a5-abb1-64deb4a15e50,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.216274,2026-03-12 09:42:25.216274,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Andy Hing,andy@shaftesbury.co.uk,\n19a3e714-af52-47a8-b79b-ba55be532aaf,Momeni,,Institutional,98b2353c-b4ac-4c8a-b021-c987917dc700,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.687295,2026-03-12 09:42:25.687295,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Send anything to Georgina.. they are well covered so probs needs to be off market/deliverable \r\ng.meyer@momeni-group.com\r\n\r\n-\tFoyles was slightly random in that it was long income (but they think tenant will leave at some point)\r\n-\tLike to buy good quality buildings in core west end that they can make best in class offices\r\n-\t£25m - £100m – 3 sources of capital – Family Office JVs (Foyles), German Insituional and balance sheet for smaller deals JV structures\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n266b6e78-4809-431f-b4f5-2a51eaeefc37,Euro Car Parks,,Institutional,d7cbef73-d93f-4968-80c8-0a16ba477e8d,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.429466,2026-03-12 09:42:25.429466,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"17/07/2023: Jason Tucker - Euro Car Parks\r\nIn growth mode. Have team across the country that can look at sites speculatively. Have track record in boosting income in car park. Also put in cameras etc. Shoreditch (for example) put on activation events to boost car park, food events etc. \r\nWill look at commercial (out of town offices with short income) if there is a parking angle (c. £5m). Will take a view on leasing / capex risk. Eg bought derelict building in Dunfermline to get parking. \r\nPrefer mngt agreements rather than lease. \r\nCan be brought in on a short term income to operate parking. Eg on development site awaiting planning.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Jason Tucker,jasontucker@eurocarparks.com,\ndc068db5-f338-480b-a016-a3bd6056a089,Evolve Estates,,Institutional,f36ddb17-39d7-4914-a3d9-0c764e5c659e,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.432311,2026-03-12 09:42:25.432311,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Sab McDonald-Hall,Smh@evolveestates.com,\need1d2a1-f2bc-4d7c-9584-4b59f6a04714,FM Investment,,Institutional,8c74da1b-f262-4aaa-b36d-1e37ae9dea35,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.47566,2026-03-12 09:42:25.47566,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"I now have an established client A who is prepared to pay 2% buyers commissions. He would like to acquire a London zone 1 retail shop with heavy footfall and with NIY north of 5%. He will consider buying either freehold or a virtual freehold property but not something with less than 500 years remaining unexpired. His budget is between GBP 3.0 to 5.0 Million.\r\n \r\nI have another established client B who is shopping for a retail shop ideally within London zone 1 but preferably still within zone 3 (with NIY north of 5.0%) but will also consider principal county towns in southern England (provided the NIY is in excess of 6.0%). His ideal budget is between GBP 1.0 to 2.0 million.\r\n \r\nI have a third established client C who is after either a boutique hotel or a luxury blocks of flats in a prime area in the West End of London. Their budget is up to GBP 50 Million. They will consider buying the hotel with hotel management in place (but with break options that would be within the next 5 -10 years). NIY should be respectable and preferably north of 4%. Ideally , if you come across a distressed sale, that would be perfect since they are prepared to pay 100% in cash with short completion time. \r\n \r\nI also have a fourth established client D who is only interested in international Grade A office bldgs. in the West End or in the City. FYI, they currently own one of the following three trophy bldgs. in the City namely the Walkie Talkie, the cheesegrater or the Gerkin. They would like to buy a fire sale office bldg. to balance their current portfolio since their current portfolio comprised some Grade A office bldgs. acquired at the height of the market back in the 2010s. They have no stated budget but anything smaller than GBP 100 Million would be too small to wet their appetite.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n1365483a-74e2-4fec-b73a-f70ea8f87089,Foundation Capital,,Institutional,34403246-ea16-4b72-b8da-9eb6085be89c,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.478261,2026-03-12 09:42:25.478261,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Joint venture with Bright Bay Real Estate, backed by Starwood\r\n- They are actively seeking industrial, logistics, or storage sites. In Park Royal and West London, they are open to sites as small as 2 acres, while for the rest of the M25 area, they prefer sites of 5 acres or more, and 7 acres or more elsewhere in the UK.\r\n- Their strategy involves underwriting the current use of the site and then working to secure power and planning for a data centre as the value-add opportunity.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n3bf5b91f-4788-4851-b189-3a5b2b6dd65d,Global Mutual,,Institutional,2a70e048-642f-4589-abf6-0987895a62e5,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.495366,2026-03-12 09:42:25.495366,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"09/01/2025\r\nCar Park Portfolio\r\n•\tHistorically, the portfolio consisted only of NCP assets and was owned by Davidson Kempner. Greenpoint bought this portfolio from DK (and now realise they overpaid).\r\n•\tGlobal Mutual manages the portfolio on behalf of Greenpoint. The portfolio mostly comprises NCP assets but now includes other operators.\r\n•\tThe portfolio is split into ‘core’ and ‘non-core’ assets. \r\no\tCore Assets: Focused on Greenpoint’s strategy of expansion, implementing EV chargers and/or potentially last-mile logistics.\r\no\tNon-Core Assets: May be sold to fund capex on the core portfolio. These assets include NCP-let car parks in secondary locations such as Colchester and Ipswich, with 16 years unexpired leases. As part of a Covid-era regear with NCP, each lease includes a landlord-only break on three months' notice, opening the possibility of conversion to alternative uses. \r\n•\tGlobal Mutual / Greenpoint is keen to keep acquiring ‘core’ car parks.\r\n•\tIf anyone has ideas for buyers who could acquire the non-core portfolio in bulk, let me know. I did say the market would be thin for this...\r\n\r\nUrban Pubs & Bars Portfolio\r\n•\tDavidson Kempner and Global Mutual acquired Urban Pubs and Bars (UP&B) in 2021. This strategy focuses on investing in high-quality UK hospitality assets, concentrated in London and the South East. It is predominantly a leasehold operating business.\r\n•\tBrands: Includes the Salt Yard Group (Spanish and Italian tapas), Bat & Ball (sports bar and games hall), and pubs like The Wheatsheaf in Tooting and The Cyclist in Balham. It also operates the \"\"Urban Locals\"\" format in urban villages such as Highgate and three City bars.\r\n•\tExpansion: In August last year, UP&B acquired 11 new sites, including eight trading leasehold businesses and three vacant freehold sites from the administrators of Elflock Limited, Babel Silk Limited, Brocade Limited, and De Gremio Limited. \r\no\tThe Bat & Ball site in Stratford serves as a blueprint for further national expansion.\r\n•\tOther Key Sites: The East Dulwich Tavern (East Dulwich), The Antelope (Tooting), and The Sun (Camberwell).\r\n•\tThey remain acquisitive for this strategy and plan to grow the concept.\r\n\r\nTavern Propco Pub Portfolio\r\n•\tDavidson Kempner bought 370 pubs previously owned by Ei Group (formerly Enterprise Inns). The majority of these are owned freehold with ‘free of tie’ (FOT) leases.\r\n•\tMost sites are independent ‘watering holes’.\r\n•\tThey remain acquisitive for this strategy.\r\n\r\nOverarching Goal\r\nThe main objective for these portfolios is to build platforms and then exit. For instance, Global Mutual is considering exiting the core car park portfolio by listing it as a REIT.\r\n\r\nAdditional Opportunities\r\n•\tGlobal Mutual is also able to provide debt, although they acknowledge the market is quite crowded.\r\n12/07/2023: Met with Christian Gomez from Global Mutual.  Interested in Biggin Hill, although will want to flip on PC rather than hold so unlikely to work. I will send when back at my desk. \r\nBuying Livingstone RP with Patron, not yet exchanged / completed. \r\nLooking at LDO, did not say who with but presumably Patron (Daniel Weisz).\r\nCarling (one of their capital sources) looking to exit UK. GM trying to line up investors for their assets (Patron likely) and recapitalise, rather than sell. These include 4 retail outlets. From memory they also own an office scheme in Cardiff. \r\nGreenpoint acquired their NCP car park portfolio, which they were AM on on behalf of Davidson Kempner. GM retained as AM. Greenpoint looking to acquire more car parks. Any ideas here?\r\nHave 5 PBSA assets, 2 of which failed to sell, where they were brought in by the lender (Wells Fargo? TBD) as AM. CBRE and KF failed the sale. \r\nRetained as AM on ex-Intu schemes. Unlikely to sell these. Refi next year and carry out 3 year business plan.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Steve Gray,sg@globalmutual.com,\n4af0e1b3-5384-4d7f-9b49-76979ffe968b,KZN Real Estate,,Institutional,62deb1d0-0414-4aba-8327-f4485772ea20,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.605778,2026-03-12 09:42:25.605778,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Aug 23 - The KZN Real Estate team believe every day presents the opportunity to improve. We apply this belief to every project and investment opportunity, in a constant pursuit of driving superior returns for partners. KZN Real Estate was established to create & deliver real estate investment value and performance, by capitalising on the economic opportunity offered by ESG. By taking assets through the 'Brown to Green Journey', we believe superior returns will be consistently delivered, and most critically, delivered in the 'right way'. We invest our own funds alongside joint venture partners to acquire real estate across all asset classes, adding value through strong stock selection, rigorous due diligence and a continuous search for improvement. We seek to work with new and established partners who share our ambitions to deliver best-in-class assets and align with our focus on sustainability. \r\nSep 6th - \r\n•\tGiven his background from NFUM, he’s looking to build a balanced portfolio across the main property sectors from spec industrial to high street.\r\n•\tTarget lot size £10-£20m.\r\n•\tIRR, value-add driven and will utilise debt.\r\n•\tNeeds to have ESG-improvement angle, and needs to have an institutional exit in mind.\r\n•\tHappy to do heavy lifting on refurbs.\r\n•\tSits in Colmore Capital’s office in Birmingham – I think he has some capital from them and is able to use their asset management / development capability as a resource.\r\n•\tSeeking further sources of capital commitments to help grow the portfolio, and is speaking to privates and family offices to help with this.\r\n•\tHe would be able to do Sainsbury’s, Reading with existing capital, but anything larger he would need to seek further capital.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n34bd2086-5a9a-4042-b6cb-697256a7ad22,IDM,,Institutional,e1f812ae-17cb-457e-8047-b01fcc9fdcda,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.551196,2026-03-12 09:42:25.551196,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Keith Davies,kd@idmproperties.com,\nee0ae900-faef-4c62-97fc-ae85d6ce85e1,Inspired Assets,,Institutional,c38c12a1-45dd-48a2-86ba-f75f1d5b3a8e,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.557099,2026-03-12 09:42:25.557099,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,Single shop 8%+,,,Mar 2026,,,,Oliver Baldwin,oliver@inspiredassets.com,\n9b0afaf8-7415-4dc1-9245-27559f9ae22a,Loftus,,Institutional,517e7303-9101-43bc-aab1-c93e45f58fe9,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.623354,2026-03-12 09:42:25.623354,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"General focuses are\r\n\r\nOffice income plays where we think we can add value grow rents (west end / city) \r\nOffice to hotel/resi conversion opportunities. Flexible on locations Zones 1 - 4 near tube stations. Don’t mind 2-3 years of income. Doesn’t need to be oven ready. Happy to take planning risk.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\ndfdd9896-04eb-4d68-8637-44f45a018376,LM Stern,,Institutional,3500f2b0-e064-4257-8f33-d9f1ba95dd49,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.617405,2026-03-12 09:42:25.617405,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Fred Meehan,fred.meehan@lmstern.com,\n100a3b19-b743-4722-9921-4c084b1cb839,New River,,Institutional,bbf7ab55-d109-4f3b-9dfe-77a684093b2d,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.710576,2026-03-12 09:42:25.710576,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Hugh Sancroft-Baker,hsancroft-baker@nrr.co.uk,\nee695c25-cb48-4d62-a9e6-0e1718e57745,Nuveen,,Institutional,dcc65143-19a4-4977-ae8b-51dd83a94be3,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.71628,2026-03-12 09:42:25.71628,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Jamie Johnson,Jamie.Johnson@threalestate.com,\n36a801df-4b5f-4ab3-a1d9-4f13dd297052,Omni Investments,,Institutional,44edeb7d-aec1-4570-97f6-9b8a2e1ec334,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.722642,2026-03-12 09:42:25.722642,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Robert G