:25.820659,2026-03-12 09:42:25.820659,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"SevenCitiesLdn is a newly formed property investment, development and asset management company, dedicated to acquiring and repositioning value-add real estate opportunities across London and top regional cities throughout the UK. Our focus is primarily on city\r\ncentres, with all uses considered - office, hotel, residential (BTR and private sale), student, leisure and retail.\r\nSevenCitiesLdn is backed by SevenCapital Plc; a leading UK real estate group and specialist in urban regeneration, known for its strong track record of delivering high-quality residential and mixed-use developments across the UK. The business has a current portfolio in\r\nexcess of £2.1 billion, equating to over 7.8 million sq ft of floorspace.\r\nTogether we are committed to transforming brownfield land and undervalued property into thriving and sustainable communities.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n8c91c03e-6fd6-4ad0-bb17-01da2d1ea896,Shaftesbury,,Institutional,6aff3867-0e14-43ce-865a-947c8023d586,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.823567,2026-03-12 09:42:25.823567,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Tom Welton,tom.welton@shaftesbury.co.uk,\nf8ee7429-5bbc-458d-96bc-cc597ada4852,Highgate Holdings,,Institutional,7ef1f209-1fad-4d9c-a114-abd58584cd61,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.528457,2026-03-12 09:42:25.528457,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Paul Rodgers,prodgers@highgatecapinv.com,\nb985a30f-2c76-4119-a982-f0cebb0d9021,Hines,,Institutional,7bf12d0c-4dd3-4d0d-9b2c-c0c70bbfc4b5,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.531592,2026-03-12 09:42:25.531592,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Jake Walsh,jake.walsh@hines.com,\ne2df841b-096d-4a25-818a-f424d55f3b88,Hunter,,Institutional,9dfaa791-0508-4f18-879f-ac5441b98d96,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.541779,2026-03-12 09:42:25.541779,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Andrew Moffat,amoffat@hunterreim.com,\nedd6296a-35e9-4a73-8db9-1e2ffe0b5cc8,Mount Anvil,,Institutional,389f5be4-b5dc-4025-a83e-95da3833d5a4,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.693529,2026-03-12 09:42:25.693529,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Richard Parker,rparker@mountanvil.com,\nc10e585d-d2e3-4ae2-a6ce-e55779e057d5,Weslyan,,Institutional,8edddffa-79ee-424a-9c62-720706912c87,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.942417,2026-03-12 09:42:25.942417,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Freehold assets only \r\n- £5m to £20m lot size\r\n- Throughout the UK\r\n- Pre-let forward commitments \r\n- Target yield 5%+ \r\n\r\nOrder of preference:\r\n1. Industrial (single let, or several tenants, EPC B+, modern construction)\r\n2. Alternatives (hotels, leisure, drive-through, education, healthcare exc. carehomes)\r\n3. ‘ESG’ led assets – £2m+ (solar parks, EV charging hubs etc)\r\n4. Retail Warehouse (solus or smaller parks)\r\n5. London Offices\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n8921d413-e1c4-495d-918d-3653ef6e8223,Internos,,Institutional,4384ea8b-bab0-4c95-b796-081f8915fcb2,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.562843,2026-03-12 09:42:25.562843,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Suburban parades, genuine neighbourhood centres. £2 -£1 m\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Richard Buxton,Richard.Buxton@internosglobal.com,\nea6e85ba-1eec-47d7-b13b-26c0f570ddb8,Investra,,Institutional,cd33e1d1-fdb2-4671-b421-719a4b2fb14d,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.568579,2026-03-12 09:42:25.568579,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Nicholas Franks,nicholas@investra.co.uk,\nf75e2226-a83c-4bee-93d0-da2e2a47f471,Areli,,Institutional,664e0442-634e-451c-8989-a444b0e7137c,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.143735,2026-03-12 09:42:25.143735,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Were interested in the retail element of Edmonton, with their UHNW pocket.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Andrea Vanni,,\n60811ec1-0ba5-47d3-8f24-a47017b7f8bd,Brydell,,Institutional,a1b398be-3b9b-4578-9f2f-7ffa32defdfe,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.203821,2026-03-12 09:42:25.203821,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Dan Kelly,kelly@brydellpartners.com,\n9b5cc659-1b4a-49d8-a9e9-4c9c16666705,Mindplace,2754903561,Active Buyers,,,\"{\"\"lat\"\": \"\"51.3769529\"\", \"\"lng\"\": \"\"-0.0956895\"\", \"\"address\"\": \"\"Croydon, UK\"\"}\",,No,2026-03-07 10:50:09.641974,2026-03-07 10:50:09.641974,f,f,f,f,f,,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\nc9dcabbc-7479-4441-9292-f8dfc3f121da,A Beautiful Company,,Institutional,4ba9b84c-a65b-483e-94a5-fa0be1152674,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.070855,2026-03-12 09:42:25.070855,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"-\tRegional offices – I’m looking for potential off market / stressed situations to buy top 10 office buildings in the top 10 regions for c.10%. AG would be the capital behind this so we’re well funded.\r\n-\tOperational real estate – health care, NHS angle, government income, or anything else alternative with a PE angle. Looking to invest £100-200m+ so the bigger the better\r\no\tFrogmore you said has some care homes?\r\n-\tMayfair offices – let me know bid dates / progress on the 3 you sent me, or if I should reach out directly to the agent.\r\n-\tMIPIM – let me know when you’re having drinks and I’ll come join you!\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n7be096f7-a733-474c-b5a9-7519aa6e6b2f,Abdn,,Institutional,1b052460-5c7d-4dc1-af9e-27860fbcb048,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.080755,2026-03-12 09:42:25.080755,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"13/11/2025\r\nDistribution and Logistics £15m to £100m\r\n. Well located, flexible Logistics Units and Parcel Hubs with  strong market demand / supply dynamics.\r\n. Urban Distribution / Collection facilities and last mile delivery units in key commercial centres.\r\n. Quality Multi-Let Estates and Trade Parks in London, the South East and strong regional locations.\r\n. Accessible locations with strong labour pools and power provision are of particular interest.\r\n. Speculative opportunities from £10m - £30m, in strong locations with flexible specifications.\r\nOffices £20m to £200m\r\n. High quality, efficient and future-proofed offices which provide flexibility and additional service provision.\r\n. Preference for multi-let, Freehold West End of London offices.\r\n. Well connected strong regional and South East locations. London offices in strong sub-markets, including potential value-add opportunities.\r\nSocial Infrastructure £5m to £50m\r\n. Primary Healthcare and related infrastructure assets.\r\n. Life Sciences including laboratories, innovation centres and high-tech offices.\r\n. Dedicated Data Centres in close proximity to major city locations.\r\n. Public and private Educational Facilities with or without accommodation.\r\n. Self-Storage, Car Parks, and Roadside Operations.\r\n. Specialised Real Estate such as energy generation, waste transfer, crematoria, sustainable woodland, solar farms, and forestry.\r\nLiving £15m to £80m\r\n. Stand alone or mixed-use Build to Rent opportunities.\r\n. Serviced Apartments in Greater London and dominant city centre locations.\r\n. Leased and direct let Student Accommodation in strong University locations.\r\n. Leased and affordable Care Homes and Senior Living in high quality schemes.\r\n. Modern Hotels and Aparthotels with OMV, turnover or index linked leases in strong locations.\r\nSecure Income £15m to £150m\r\n. Investment grade covenants for an average lease length in excess of 15 years.\r\n. Preference for inflation linked or fixed increase review structures.\r\n. Commercial Ground Rents with inflation linked review structures.\r\nSupermarkets and Retail Warehousing £5m to £75m\r\n. Right sized Supermarkets which offer omnichannel solutions with strong trading performance, let off affordable rents.\r\n. Retail warehousing let off re-based rents and with a discount, food, or convenience orientated line up.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n8bbe729d-0f65-48ce-9f39-de0fba4e0fa0,ADIA,,Institutional,d25fa4ba-915b-4731-bbdb-4dd662c4a950,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.087359,2026-03-12 09:42:25.087359,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Tom Pope,tom.pope@adia.ae,\ncc9ca39e-a944-40fa-9bc6-38e846f99d41,AEW,,Institutional,177a717a-2967-4a8c-bf84-9e651c607724,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.090079,2026-03-12 09:42:25.090079,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Laura Elkin,laura.elkin@aeweurope.com,\n7c9d0da7-737c-4b78-88cd-68f461f7c