y want opportunistic stuff in the Wet End, any sector, minimum lot size £50m. They bid on Langham yesterday…. @Woody Bruce Gibbo was acting for them on the offices did you do the retail for him in the end?? They were looking at a ground lease on Outernet interestingly?!?\r\n\r\nThey obviously love RBS and the leasing team so happy to be guided by us on the retail and where to target.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\nb683c98c-166f-43d3-b46f-b03006bddf17,Aviva Investors,,Institutional,4dda4ce1-faff-4ad7-bbd6-83c17e4205c5,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.162211,2026-03-12 09:42:25.162211,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Like single family, like platforms. Invested in UK affordable.\r\n14/03/2023:\r\n- WIP with Charlie Littlemore\r\n- Works on long income transactions and Assistant Fund Manager on Aviva Life and Pens Fund \r\n- Aviva Life and Pens ultimate aim is to outpace MSCI by 50bps\r\n- Essex County Council and UKGI - £1bn each\r\n- Heritage Friends Life - managed by Ed Fuller - looking to track MSCI\r\n- New fund (TBD name) - absolute return fund (6% net of fees)\r\n- Not acquisitive til H2 this year\r\n- Internal capital funds are acquisitive at the moment\r\n- £400m capital to deploy this year - sat on £830m cash atm\r\n- £35-£80/90m lot size on single assets, can go higher for portfolios\r\n- Want income return that can complement development pipeline (Liverpool St / Moorgate and Packaged Living)\r\n- 10 year plus leases, not many lease events in next 3-4 years, happy to take on OMRRs\r\n- Targeting +6-7% unlevered IRR\r\n- Used to be 5 year holds, more flex in this now\r\n- Sector agnostic, although looking to reduce exposure on offices\r\n- Can do pre-let forward fundings, but no spec dev\r\n- Assess location on deal by deal basis, not as constrained as they once were\r\n- Long income\r\n  - Focus is income strips and ground rents \r\n  - Annuity book is in buy mode at the moment\r\n  - Ground rents can do 15% gearing\r\n- Overweight in cash so unlikely to be sellers\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Sean Moran,Sean.Moran@avivainvestors.com,\n7f232a44-d203-4284-9e7c-04a4899243b3,AXA,,Institutional,2cd13913-c8df-4e9f-9ee0-5909ebd0e685,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.165304,2026-03-12 09:42:25.165304,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"06.06.2022:\r\n\r\nMeeting with John O’Driscoll who runs UK & Europe. Several pockets ranging from core, core plus to value add. Not shy on development as we know. Are hiring someone to help Stuart Carr Jones so they have more UK bandwith.\r\n\r\nBTR not found a platform yet that works from a fees and pricing perspective. SF can’t do given reputational risk. Own Retirement Villages which are largely southern based and largely BTS so one of the seniors operators in the North or more advanced in BTR would be interesting.\r\n\r\nHave a €4bn open ended fund for logistics that issues unsecured debt so very competitive. Own Data4, pan European DC developer and operator, looking for more UK sites. Like core offices, no interest in secondary.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Staurt Carr Jones,Stuart.Carr-Jones@axa-im.com,\n70e518a7-da61-4a96-aee3-cd5e1a4eed4f,Barings,,Institutional,bda0fd7a-2a3f-4f52-a0db-4b12af1bfef5,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.167916,2026-03-12 09:42:25.167916,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Darren Hutchinson,Darren.hutchinson@barings.com,\n67c64175-e355-41b6-ad78-618a6402eac8,Blackrock,,Institutional,d289b58d-42f0-4957-b4e3-fad40981e284,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.171632,2026-03-12 09:42:25.171632,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Geoffrey Shaw,geoffrey.shaw@blackrock.com,\ne56f486e-4bc3-4869-af4c-c81925e5a3c1,Blue Coast Capital,,Institutional,3bedb767-9be3-4e6a-913a-56fff4187ee1,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.174819,2026-03-12 09:42:25.174819,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Ben Beck,bbeck@bccap.com,\nce96cb2a-7dbc-412d-9552-9c1b598a4f66,Bond Wolfe,,Institutional,d07a7895-8575-477f-83e8-1402278ee958,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.184904,2026-03-12 09:42:25.184904,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Bobby Bassi,bobbybassi@bondwolfe.net,\nebd32df0-d236-45ea-b684-8e866a312bad,Bravo Investments,,Institutional,b3f47590-6e6f-4789-a808-85a0d159e2d5,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.190565,2026-03-12 09:42:25.190565,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"Commercial, hotel. £5-£25mn. M25 or crossrail\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Jaclyn Jesus,jaclyn@bravo-investment.com,\n6ea09b91-985e-4b2e-a7bb-26e82416a285,British Land,,Institutional,5eac4fda-83c8-44ff-8f63-b71128ca0f7a,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.193601,2026-03-12 09:42:25.193601,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Kelly Cleveland,kelly.cleveland@britishland.com,\nc456a917-7e3b-4bfe-ae51-11f71f1efd79,Brockton,,Institutional,9e8ca5a8-f45c-46f4-9d0d-1171f3a822e3,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.197262,2026-03-12 09:42:25.197262,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,James Spencer,spencer@brocktoneverlast.com,\n77037751-97be-4439-a51b-859c25d72049,Dorrington,,Institutional,9e3df74a-fef8-4730-a9f8-a4ed126d669d,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.400388,2026-03-12 09:42:25.400388,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"•\tBuildings with VP or short term income \r\n•\tSuitable for serviced office implementation (we look at the floor plate, where the core is situated and window line) \r\n•\t30,000 sq ft plus. \r\n•\tCore Zone 1 locations \r\n•\tWould look at West End but can’t be too expensive\r\n•\tCapital value has to be low enough to warrant a £500 psf plus spend on fit out. \r\n•\tGood ‘bones’ of building\",,,Mar 2026,,,,,,\n412e324b-b94d-4108-ba75-e806312ed875,Castleforge,,Institutional,c3844962-ee6d-4d1d-8bb6-4ad06cfb817b,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.222293,2026-03-12 09:42:25.222293,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Michael Kovacs,mkovacs@castleforgepartners.com,\n3f1d0199-a370-4547-a0c0-2d1b868ab6f5,CBRE IM,,Institutional,c5762d6d-8acd-478a-a0c6-c5f2cb937fa0,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.22511,2026-03-12 09:42:25.22511,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,\"16.11.2022 \r\nCap Markets WIP notes - John Quere (Director, Transactions)\r\n•\tTeam structure: Tom James leads transaction function in UK, and Jon Quere (Director) supports him\r\n•\tRole of team is to support capital markets business to originate and execute transactions\r\no\tUK Discretionary Capital - all equity\r\no\tInbound capital - pooled funds from across business, European / global separate accounts\r\n•\tBeds and sheds sector is primary focus - opportunistic requirements in other sectors\r\n•\tGlobal Alpha is CBRE's flagship global fund, GAV c. £10bn - have allocated 300m in equity to invest in UK (unlikely to take debt at present)\r\no\tResidential and core plus shopping centre is key focus - can do direct but not afraid of minority or majority JVs\r\no\tTargeting double digit returns\r\n•\tPan-European Core Fund (PEC)\r\no\tCore logistics, West End prime offices, residential (stabilised and forward commit - not fundings at present)\r\no\t£300m equity for UK, plus extra from debt\r\no\tRevolving green debt facility with fixed low interest rate\r\no\tTargeting core returns between 6 and 7% unlevered returns\r\n•\tELP (European Logistics Properties) - formed by merger of 2 existing CBRE IM funds\r\no\tRaised 6-700m of equity to invest in Europe, 200m for UK\r\no\tTargeting spec logistics development, return requirements value add, late single digits over ten year period\r\no\tQuite active now that logistics land pricing has come off\r\no\tGDV >50m, build-to-core strategy in top-tier locations. Will form JVs with best in class operators.\r\n•\tAll 3 funds above are ready to invest today\r\n•\tEuropean Residential Impact Fund \r\no\tNewly formed\r\no\t£700m of equity to invest across Europe\r\no\t£50m per year next 5 years, London and key cities\r\no\tAs with PEC, fundings difficult at present - stabilised and forward commits favourable\r\no\t£30-100m lot size, core/core+\r\n•\tEPF (Malaysia)\r\no\tMalaysian restrictions mean cannot convert MY currency into GBP so not able to invest at present\r\no\tHowever, expected to lift this restriction in next few months - keen to invest\r\no\tReturn requirements have come down, so may be competitive\r\no\tMonitoring offices (Central London) and logistics\r\n•\tWithin UK, split into two buckets:\r\no\tConventional - £700m of requirements in UK made up of 3 or 4 key clients\r\n•\tHampshire - opportunity-led, £200m to invest as at today, stabilised resi, PBSA, core logistics\r\n•\tWest Midlands - opportunity-led, full on offices, easier return requirement than Hampshire so less risk needed\r\n•\tUnilever PF - 100% best-in-class ESG assets (or opportunities to create these assets), offices and keen to see stock in beds sector\r\n•\tUK Affordable Housing Fund - £200m equity to invest today, plan is to continue to grow the fund as quickly as possible\r\no\tLong Income - £200m to invest across 2 or 3 key clients\r\n•\tSupermarkets, logistics, and possibly leased hotels\r\n•\tTo summarise, significant amount of capital to invest across business - opportunity-led but patient.\",,,Mar 2026,,,,Will Middleton,william.middleton@cbreglobalinvestors.com,\n2cb2cfcd-8f3c-46e7-b1b2-91c2450f2313,Cervidae,,Institutional,1a2e8b42-1a2b-45f2-8221-a6389f2af4f1,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.235395,2026-03-12 09:42:25.235395,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Alex Hamilton,alex@cervidae.co.uk,\n35bf625c-3cd4-4b98-a4f2-1e540a7b5e39,Charles Street,,Institutional,80f132f8-e048-4510-bba6-a3b7c2d6fd07,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.238306,2026-03-12 09:42:25.238306,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Joseph Murphy,joseph.murphy@csbgroup.co.uk,\n4785b1fb-ac3b-427d-80e8-c2b5c1f7fe88,Citivest,,Institutional,3f69b263-1a35-463d-90f1-e911f5ae9c2d,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.247554,2026-03-12 09:42:25.247554,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,,,,Mar 2026,,,,Nathan Sugar,nathan@citivest.co.uk,\ndecf54cb-f4f5-4655-be9a-2c0eba35e5e9,Clearbell,,Institutional,d146f3af-8a8f-45fe-9e6e-90d1ee2ead62,,,,,2026-03-12 09:42:25.250807,2026-03-12 09:42:25.250807,f,f,f,f,f,Active,,,,,We can go up to £50m on London offices however would prefer if the property was income producing and not VP.,,,Mar 2026,,,,Rob Cole,robertc@clearbell.com,\n4a71261a-1375-424d-8dcf-9fb043071386,Colmore Capital,,Institution